#!/bin/sh

set -eu

cat <<'EOF'
Dotfiles help

Shell
- primary shell: zsh; fallback shell: bash
- startup order: .zshenv -> .shell/core -> .shell/optional -> .shell/local -> shell-specific rc/login files
- portable shell layers live in ~/.shell/core and ~/.shell/optional
- machine-local overrides belong in ~/.shell/local
- common defaults: Ctrl-a start of line, Ctrl-e end of line, Ctrl-r history search, Ctrl-w delete word, Ctrl-l clear screen
- fzf helpers: Ctrl-r=fuzzy command history, fh=pick a past command into the prompt
- filesystem helpers: md=create and enter a directory, extract=unpack common archive formats
- zsh vi mode: Esc enters normal mode, i/a return to insert mode
- after install, select MesloLGS NF, FiraCode, or JetBrains Mono in the terminal profile
- bootstrap attempts to switch the login shell to zsh automatically for the current user
- ~/.p10k.zsh is linked to the repo, so running p10k configure updates the tracked theme file

Tmux
- prefix: Ctrl-s
- common defaults: prefix c=new window, prefix d=detach, prefix n/p=next/prev window, prefix z=zoom pane, prefix ?=list bindings
- panes: prefix v=split below, prefix h=split right, Alt-q=kill pane, prefix b=break pane into window
- pane movement: Ctrl-h/j/k/l
- window movement: Alt-h/l
- common window shortcuts: Alt-n=new window, Ctrl-PageUp/Down=prev/next window, prefix ,=rename window
- pane resize: Alt-Arrow
- layouts and copy mode: Alt-space=next layout, Alt-c=copy mode, copy-mode y=copy selection
- bundled helpers: tmux-fzf-url=open URLs from pane history, vim-tmux-navigator=shared Ctrl-h/j/k/l movement with Neovim
- shell aliases: ta=attach, tat=attach target, tls=list sessions, tns=new named session, tm=smart attach/create session picker, tm -d=detach other clients first
- reload config: tmux source-file ~/.tmux.conf

Neovim
- leader: Space
- split movement: Ctrl-h/j/k/l
- buffer movement: Alt-h/l
- split resize: Alt-Arrow
- common defaults: :q close window, :w write file, u undo, Ctrl-r redo, / search, n/N next/prev match
- direct Vim split movement fallback: Ctrl-w h/j/k/l
- default plugins: fugitive/fubitive/rhubarb/fugitive-gitlab=git workflows; signify=diff signs; lualine=statusline; sandwich/sleuth/repeat/nerdcommenter/lexima/editing helpers; gundo=undo tree; better-whitespace=trim trailing spaces; visual-star-search=search visual selections; suda=sudo write; direnv/rooter/localvimrc=project env/root detection
- advanced Neovim layer: cmp+nvim-lsp+vsnip=completions; treesitter=syntax/tree parsing; fzf-lua=fuzzy finding via :Files/:Buffers/:Lines/:RG; dap/dap-ui/dap-python/dap-go=debugging; lf.vim=file manager; togglelist/qf_resize/window-swap=window and list helpers
- markdown support: preservim/vim-markdown with tabular for tables and frontmatter support
- file navigation: :E/:Explore uses netrw, q closes netrw, - moves up, <leader>e uses lf.vim, :Files and :Buffers use fzf-lua
- dispatch: :Dispatch <cmd> runs async jobs in Neovim via dispatch-neovim
- filetype plugins: Dockerfile, nix, rust, toml, orgmode, tex/vimtex, json/jsonc/json5/jsonnet, jinja, asciidoctor, csv, neomutt, syncthing, nftables, bitbake, vala, solidity, mediawiki, pydoc
- advanced layer can be disabled with NVIM_PORTABLE_BASE_ONLY=1
- host-only behavior belongs in ~/.config/nvim/host-specific

Git
- portable defaults live in ~/.config/git/config
- machine-local identity lives in ~/.local/share/git/config
- useful aliases: st=status, br=branch, co=checkout, cmt=commit, lg=pretty log, shorty=status --short --branch

Mail
- msmtp is the backend transport for scripts and notifications
- mutt/neomutt is the interactive mail layer on top of msmtp
- local mail files:
  - ~/.config/msmtp/config
  - ~/.local/share/mutt/private.rc

Post-install
- guided local setup: setup-local-machine
- checklist: post-install-checklist
- GitHub auth: gh auth login
- terminal-specific key discovery: run zkbd inside a real zsh terminal if needed and save it as ~/.zkbd/$TERM

Verification
- repo verification: ./verify-bootstrap.sh
- bootstrap dry-run: ./bootstrap.sh --dry-run

Packages
- baseline everywhere: shell/core CLI, prompt fonts, search/navigation tools, Neovim, tmux, storage/network filesystem support
- full profile adds: nala, mutt+msmtp, lf, taskwarrior, and extra shell integrations

Scripts
- local-only scripts belong in ~/bin
- shared repo scripts are installed at ~/bin/shared
- both are on PATH, with ~/bin first
- shared helpers include: tm, now, post-install-checklist, setup-local-machine, dotfiles-help
- diff helper: vdiff left right (files => nvim -d, directories => DirDiff)

Where to edit
- shell docs: ~/.shell/README.md
- tmux docs: ~/.tmux/README.md
- Neovim docs: ~/.config/nvim/README.md
- git docs: ~/.config/git/README.md
- install docs: INSTALL.md
EOF
